NAME
    reverse_array - reverse the order of an array
 
SYNOPSIS
    #include <acme.h>
    static inherit AcmeArray;
    #include AcmeArrayInc

    mixed *reverse_array( mixed *arr );
 
DESCRIPTION
    Reverses the order of an array.  Since arrays are passed by 
    reference, this changes the original.  Returns a pointer to
    the array, just to be nice.
 
EXAMPLE
    reverse_array( ({ 1, 2, 3 }) )  ->  ({ 3, 2, 1 })
 
